      <section xml:id="sec-Advancedlearningobjectives11">
        <title>Advanced learning objectives</title>

        <p>
          In addition to mastering the basic objectives, here are the tasks you should be able 
          to perform, with practice:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
      Explain why antidifferentiation works as a universal method when <m>f</m> depends only 
      on <m>x</m>, using the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
      Express solutions with initial conditions using definite-integral form 
      <m>y(x) = \int_{x_0}^{x} f(s)\,ds + y_0</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
      Articulate the conceptual difference between the definite integral (a number) and 
      the indefinite integral (a family of antiderivatives).
            </p>
          </li>

        </ul>

      </section>


